# Deploy workflow (default)

User confirmed auto-deploy for this project (2026-07-19). After finishing implementation or bugfix tasks, **commit and push to `main` automatically** unless the user explicitly says not to (e.g. "don't commit", "로컬만", "커밋하지 마", "배포하지 마").

## Steps

1. Run `git status` / `git diff` — do not commit secrets, `.env`, or unused scratch files (e.g. `getApiErrorMessage.ts`).
2. Update `.cursor/handoff/latest.json` + `LATEST_TEST_HANDOFF.md` for the 프로그램테스트 agent (see `test-handoff` rule).
3. Commit with a clear message (why, not just what).
4. Push `origin main` to trigger GitHub Pages frontend deploy.
5. If `backend/` or `shared/` changed, remind that Render redeploy is needed (Deploy Hook workflow or Render dashboard).
6. Point the user at 프로그램테스트: https://cursor.com/agents/bc-019f7d59-bc4b-7526-a842-4068cf31def4 and the handoff files.

## When to skip auto-deploy

- User-only questions / reviews with no code changes
- User explicitly forbids commit or push
- No meaningful changes to commit
